<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-635-433  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 635 433.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  Dec 1990 v15 n13 p327(6).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Concurrent C. (language for multiprocessor programming)(technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gehani, Narain H.; Roome, William D.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>A concurrent version of the C programming language that supportsmultiprocessor computer architectures is discussed.andP;  Concurrent Cis a superset of C that is upward compatible and provides parallelprogramming facilities.andP;  An application written in Concurrent Cconsists of a set of processes that send messages to each otherand execute in parallel.andP;  The new language uses the 'extendedrendezvous' concept under which two processes establish a point ofsynchronization and exchange information before continuing theirseparate activities.andP;  Some users nevertheless prefer asynchronousmessage-passing models; the language provides enough flexibilityto permit the use of shared memory on proper hardware.andP;  ConcurrentC is a compile-time option that works either with standard C orC++.andP;  The incorporation of object-oriented structures such asclasses into Concurrent C is discussed.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     C Programming LanguageMultiprocessingConcurrent ProgrammingTechnologyProgramming Languages.andO;Feature:   illustrationprogram.andO;Caption:   lockMngr process. (program)diskScheduler process. (program)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>